Financial services company Liberty Holding on Tuesday announced the resignation of its group financial director, Casper Troskie. “Troskie leaves after 7 years of service, in order to pursue a new opportunity at a competitor of Liberty,” the company said. “Mr Troskie’s resignation is with immediate effect but is subject to a contractual three month notice period during which time Mr Troskie will be available to Liberty,” it said. Liberty Holding said that the appointment of his successor will be subject to the appropriate processes including the finalisation of regulatory and administrative approvals. Read: Liberty reports lower earnings but improved cash flow